```
file: crates/ctx-context/src/session.rs
behavior: Tracks which context node ids have already been injected for a given Claude session, backed by one gitignored JSON file per session under `.context/.cache/`, to prevent duplicate hook injections on repeated Read/Grep/Glob calls.
edit_notes:
  - CLI path mode reads ENV_SESSION_ID to share the same served-node ledger as `--hook` mode; keep the state file format/location compatible with both.
  - load() treats missing or corrupt state files as empty (fail-open by design) — never make this path return an error or block.
functions:
  - name: load
    signature: pub fn load<E: Env>(env: &E, session: &str) -> BTreeSet<String>
    purpose: Reads the set of node ids already served for `session`, defaulting to empty on any failure.
  - name: save
    signature: pub fn save<E: Env>(env: &E, session: &str, served: &BTreeSet<String>) -> Result<(), CtxError>
    purpose: Persists the full served-node set for `session` as JSON.
  - name: record
    signature: pub fn record<E: Env>(env: &E, session: &str, ids: impl IntoIterator<Item = String>) -> Result<(), CtxError>
    purpose: Merges new node ids into the session's served set and persists the result.
invariants:
  - state_path sanitizes session ids to [A-Za-z0-9._-], replacing all other characters with '_'.
  - load() never panics or errors; missing/corrupt files yield an empty BTreeSet.
external_deps:
  - serde_json: (de)serializes the served-id set to/from the cache file.
```